Chris Eppstein wrote:

&gt; Does anyone know of any utilities that can check for test coverage. This
&gt; could be a simple as an Ant task or maybe a more complicated plug-in for
&gt; JUnit or even a stand alone utility. Any ideas? I&#39;d like to not re-invent
&gt; the wheel if something like this exists already.
&gt;

Hi Chris,

I had good success with NoUnit.  It measures method-level coverage exercised by
JUnit tests only, as far as I can tell, so if you&#39;re looking for statement and
branch coverage it won&#39;t hit the mark.

    http://nounit.sourceforge.net/

Here&#39;s the Ant task I used:

    &lt;target name=&quot;coverage&quot; depends=&quot;compile, compile-tests&quot;&gt;

        &lt;java fork=&quot;yes&quot;

classname=&quot;net.firstpartners.nounit.ui.command.CommandLineProcessor&quot;&gt;
            &lt;classpath&gt;
                &lt;path location=&quot;./lib/nounit.jar&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;path location=&quot;./lib/jdom.jar&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;path location=&quot;./lib/xml.jar&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;path location=&quot;./lib/xalan.jar&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;path location=&quot;./lib/xerces.jar&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;path location=&quot;./lib/jclasslib.jar&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;/classpath&gt;
            &lt;arg line=&quot;start_dir ${classes.dir}&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;arg line=&quot;output_dir ${docs.dir}&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;arg line=&quot;report_class
net.firstpartners.nounit.report.CallsReport&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;arg line=&quot;report_name c:/tools/nounit/xslt/no-unit.xsl&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;arg line=&quot;output_file TestCoverage.html&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;/java&gt;
    &lt;/target&gt;

Hope this helps.

